# sys-monitor-tauri ‚Äî Cursor Rules & Architectural Source of Truth

## 1. Project Overview & Core Stack

Real-time Windows desktop system monitor built with Tauri v1. A single Rust backend collects CPU, memory, disk, network, and GPU metrics via Win32 PDH/WMI/NVAPI, streams them at 1 Hz over Tauri IPC, and a React/TypeScript frontend renders live area charts with drag-to-reorder cards. **Windows only** ‚Äî every collector depends on Win32-exclusive APIs.

| Layer | Technology | Version |
|---|---|---|
| App shell | Tauri v1 (WebView2) | `tauri = "1"` |
| Backend | Rust 2021, `sysinfo 0.33`, `windows 0.52` (PDH), `wmi 0.13`, `nvapi-sys 0.1.3` (opt) | edition 2021 |
| Frontend | React 18, TypeScript 5, Vite 5 | `"react": "^18.2.0"`, `"vite": "^5.0.0"` |
| Charts | Recharts 3 (`AreaChart` + `Area`) | `"recharts": "^3.8.0"` |
| Drag-and-drop | @dnd-kit/core, @dnd-kit/sortable, @dnd-kit/utilities | `"@dnd-kit/core": "^6.3.1"` |
| Serialization | serde + serde_json | `"1"` |

**Cargo features:**
- `nvapi` (default ON) ‚Äî Nvidia GPU temp via NVAPI. Guard all Nvidia code with `#[cfg(feature = "nvapi")]`.
- `custom-protocol` ‚Äî production bundles; never remove.

---

## CI Readiness Gate

Every task that modifies Rust or frontend code MUST pass all of the
following checks before the task is considered complete. Do not
summarise a task as done until every applicable check below passes.

### When Rust files are changed (src-tauri/**):
Run from sys-monitor-tauri/src-tauri:
  cargo build --verbose
  cargo test --verbose
  cargo fmt -- --check
  cargo clippy --verbose -- -D warnings

If cargo fmt -- --check fails:
  Run: cargo fmt
  Then re-run: cargo fmt -- --check to confirm clean.
  Always commit formatted files ‚Äî never leave unformatted Rust.

If cargo clippy -- -D warnings fails:
  Fix every warning. Do not add #[allow(...)] to suppress warnings
  unless the suppression is conditional (#[cfg_attr(...)]) and
  explicitly justified in a comment.

### When frontend files are changed (src/**):
Run from sys-monitor-tauri:
  npx tsc --noEmit
  npm test -- --run

npm ci is run by CI but not required locally if node_modules exists.
If node_modules is missing or package.json changed: run npm install.

### When both Rust and frontend files are changed:
Run all checks from both sections above.

### Commit hygiene:
- Never commit with cargo fmt -- --check failing
- Never commit with cargo clippy -- -D warnings failing
- Never commit with npx tsc --noEmit failing
- Never commit with npm test -- --run failing
- Always run the applicable checks after the final code change and
  before writing the task summary

### Test counts (as of last audit):
- Rust: 44 tests expected. If count drops, investigate before committing.
- Frontend: 33 tests expected. If count drops, investigate before committing.

