### File placement rules
- **New Rust collector**: add `{metric}.rs` in `collector/`, re-export from `collector/mod.rs`, wire into `poll()` and `commit()`
- **New IPC payload field**: add to struct in `main.rs`, update `build_snapshot()` and `build_history_payload()`, mirror in `types/metrics.ts`
- **New React component**: `src/components/{ComponentName}.tsx` ‚Äî named export only
- **New hook**: `src/hooks/use{Name}.ts`
- **New type**: `src/types/{domain}.ts`
- **Utilities**: `src/utils.ts` (keep flat, one file)

---

## Architecture Invariants ‚Äî do not violate

- CollectorState is NEVER behind a Mutex ‚Äî background thread owns it directly
- Single PdhCollectQueryData per tick ‚Äî called once before all counter reads
- PDH handles opened once in CollectorState::new() ‚Äî never recreated mid-run
- WMIConnection is !Send ‚Äî must stay on the background thread only
- Mutex lock held only for commit + build_snapshot ‚Äî microseconds only
- Always use .unwrap_or_else(|e| e.into_inner()) on mutex locks (poison-safe)
- push_history() always used for VecDeque appends ‚Äî never push directly
- All #[cfg(feature = "nvapi")] and #[cfg(feature = "nvml")] blocks preserved
- schema_version must stay in sync: SCHEMA_VERSION (Rust) == EXPECTED_SCHEMA_VERSION (TS) == 1
- All push_history writes must happen on full ticks (1Hz) only.
  Providers may poll at 250ms for live snapshot freshness but must
  never commit to history more than once per second.
  Violation: chart scroll rate mismatch at long time windows (CPU bug, fixed).
  Implementation: registry.commit_all is gated inside
  `if let Some(ref r) = raw` so it only runs on full ticks.
  Any new sensor provider added in future must follow the same rule.

---

## 3. State Management & Data Flow

### Backend (Rust)

**Lock-scope discipline ‚Äî DO NOT violate:**
- `CollectorState` owns all OS handles, lives on the background thread, **never behind a Mutex**.
- `HistoryStore` is the **only** type behind `Mutex<HistoryStore>` (aliased as `SafeHistoryStore` / `SafeAppState`).
- Poll loop (1 Hz):
  1. `collector::poll()` ‚Äî all slow Win32 I/O, **no lock held** ‚Üí produces `RawPoll`
  2. Lock ‚Üí `collector::commit()` (pure memory writes, microseconds) ‚Üí `build_snapshot()` ‚Üí Unlock
  3. `app_handle.emit("metrics-update", snapshot)` ‚Äî NOT emit_all (removed in Tauri v2)

**Violating this by holding the lock during PDH/WMI calls will cause UI jank.**

**PDH handles opened once**: `PdhHandles` created in `CollectorState::new()`, never recreated. Recreating resets rate-counter baselines (first reading always 0%).

**WMI on MTA background thread**: winit/Tauri initializes COM as STA on main thread. `WMIConnection::new()` must run on the spawned background thread. Never move `WMIConnection` to main thread.

**OnceLock for one-time error logging**: `OnceLock<()>` on `CollectorState` for noisy per-poll errors. `get_or_init(|| eprintln!(...))` prints once, then silent.

**Ring buffers**: `VecDeque<f64>` capacity 3600 (1 hour √ó 1 Hz). Always use `push_history(deque, value, MAX_HISTORY)` ‚Äî never push directly. `MAX_HISTORY = 3600` in `collector/mod.rs`.

### Frontend (React + TypeScript)

**No external state library** ‚Äî all state is React `useState`/`useEffect` inside `useMetrics` hook and `App.tsx`.

`useMetrics(windowSeconds)` is the **single source of truth**:
- `invoke("get_history", { window_secs })` on mount and on window change ‚Üí full history snapshot
- `listen("metrics-update")` ‚Üí incremental appends via `appendToHistory` / `mergeDiskHistory` / `mergeGpuHistory`
- Returns `SlicedHistory` (windowed view) or `null` while loading
- `sliceWindow()` clips to the active time range before returning

**Browser dev mode**: `isTauri()` detects `window.__TAURI__`. When absent, `useMetrics` generates sine-wave mock data with `setInterval(1000)`. Mock data must cover all card types realistically.

**No server-state caching library** (no React Query / SWR) ‚Äî data is push-based via Tauri events.

---

## 4. Coding Standards & Conventions

### Rust

| Rule | Convention |
|---|---|
| Case | `snake_case` everywhere (Rust standard); struct fields match serde JSON keys |
| Section banners | `// ‚îÄ‚îÄ SECTION TITLE ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ` for major sections (match existing) |
| Diagnostics | `eprintln!("[Module] message")` for operational logs (Tauri dev console) |
| Unsafe blocks | Must have `// SAFETY:` comment explaining pointer validity and lifetime |
| Error handling | Prefer `Option<T>` over panics for fallible OS queries; callers use `.unwrap_or(0.0)` |
| Payload derives | `#[derive(serde::Serialize, Clone)]` on IPC structs; no `Deserialize` needed |
| Feature gates | All NVAPI code behind `#[cfg(feature = "nvapi")]`, including the stub fallback |
| Formatting | `cargo fmt` enforced in CI |
| Linting | `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` enforced in CI ‚Äî zero warnings allowed |
| Mutex recovery | `lock().unwrap_or_else(\|e\| e.into_inner())` to recover from poisoned mutex |

### TypeScript / React

| Rule | Convention |
|---|---|
| Exports | **Named exports only** ‚Äî no `export default` from component/hook files |
| Exception | `App.tsx` uses `export default function App()` (Vite convention) |
| Styling | **Inline React styles** ‚Äî no CSS modules, no Tailwind, no styled-components |
| CSS files | `styles.css` for global resets/scrollbar only; `App.css` is legacy (unused except logo hover) |
| Color palette | `#141414` background, `#1e1e1e` cards, `#4699e8` blue accent, `#4ed87a` green memory |
| Charts | `<Area isAnimationActive={false}>` always ‚Äî live data at 1-second updates cannot animate |
| Components | `PascalCase` filenames and export names (e.g. `MetricCard.tsx` ‚Üí `export function MetricCard`) |
| Hooks | `camelCase` with `use` prefix (e.g. `useMetrics.ts` ‚Üí `export function useMetrics`) |
| Types file | `types/metrics.ts` ‚Äî interfaces mirroring Rust serde structs; keep in sync manually (no codegen) |
| Strict TS | `strict: true`, `noUnusedLocals`, `noUnusedParameters`, `noFallthroughCasesInSwitch` |
| Module system | ESM (`"type": "module"` in package.json), ES2022 target |

## IPC Contract ‚Äî Tauri v2

- Rust command parameters are snake_case (e.g. window_secs: u64)
- Tauri v2 serialises these as camelCase in JS: invoke('cmd', { windowSecs: value })
- Mismatch causes silent invoke failure ‚Äî history stays null, UI hangs
- Use app_handle.emit("event", &payload) ‚Äî NOT emit_all (removed in Tauri v2)
- window.__TAURI_INTERNALS__ detects Tauri v2 runtime (NOT window.__TAURI__)

## Plugin versions ‚Äî Tauri v1 vs v2

- Tauri v1 store npm package: tauri-plugin-store-api
- Tauri v2 store npm package: @tauri-apps/plugin-store
- This project is on Tauri v2
- @tauri-apps/api v2 import path: @tauri-apps/api/core (NOT @tauri-apps/api/tauri)

### Anti-patterns to avoid

- **Never** hold `SafeHistoryStore` lock during I/O (PDH, WMI, sysinfo refresh)
- **Never** recreate `PdhHandles` after init ‚Äî rate counters lose their baseline
- **Never** move `WMIConnection` off its creation thread (COM thread affinity)
- **Never** push directly to a history `VecDeque` ‚Äî always use `push_history()`
- **Never** add CSS class-based styling to components ‚Äî use inline `style` props
- **Never** use `export default` in component files (exception: `App.tsx`)
- **Never** enable Recharts animation on live-updating charts
- **Never** add `Deserialize` derive to IPC payload structs (they only go backend ‚Üí frontend)

---

## 5. Error Handling & Validation

### Rust error handling

- **OS query failures**: return `Option<T>` / `None`; callers supply fallbacks (`.unwrap_or(0.0)`, `.unwrap_or_default()`)
- **PDH API status codes**: check `!= 0` before reading output; return empty `HashMap` on failure
- **WMI connection**: exponential backoff retry (base 1s, max 30s, 8 attempts) with per-attempt `eprintln!`
- **Noisy per-poll errors**: `OnceLock<()>` + `get_or_init(|| eprintln!(...))` to log once
- **Mutex poisoning**: `unwrap_or_else(|e| e.into_inner())` to recover and continue
- **Unsafe FFI**: every `unsafe` block must have `// SAFETY:` comment; check return codes before dereferencing

### Frontend error handling

- `invoke()` / `listen()` failures: `.catch()` with `console.warn`; UI shows "Collecting metrics‚Ä¶" while `null`
- No validation library (Zod/Yup) ‚Äî data comes from trusted Rust backend over IPC, not user input
- Null/NaN guards in formatters: `formatTempC` handles `null | undefined | NaN`, `formatResponseMs` handles `0 | Infinity`

---

## 6. Testing Strategy

### Rust tests

**Framework**: built-in `#[cfg(test)]` + `cargo test` (no external test framework).

**Location**: co-located at the bottom of each source file in `#[cfg(test)] mod tests { use super::*; ... }`.

**Pattern**: Arrange-Act-Assert with `assert_eq!` / `assert!` / `assert!(matches!(...))`.

**What to test**:
- Pure functions with deterministic outputs: string parsing, math conversions, ring-buffer logic
- Boundary conditions: empty input, overflow, off-by-one, range edges
- PDH/WMI functions requiring real Windows handles are **not** unit-tested; their pure parsing helpers are
- NVAPI smoke test: `query_nvidia_gpu_temp` returns `None` gracefully when unavailable

**Run**:
```powershell
cd sys-monitor-tauri/src-tauri
cargo test                        # all tests
cargo test test_name              # single test
cargo test collector::disk::tests # one module
```

### Frontend tests

**Vitest** (33 tests in `utils.test.ts`, `useMetrics.test.ts`). When adding tests:
- Place adjacent to file under test: `useMetrics.test.ts`, `utils.test.ts`
- Test pure utility functions (`historyMinMax`, `sliceWindow`, `appendToHistory`, formatters in `App.tsx`)
- Mock Tauri IPC for hook tests (`vi.mock('@tauri-apps/api/event')`)

### CI

GitHub Actions (`.github/workflows/rust.yml`) on `windows-latest`:
1. `cargo build --verbose`
2. `cargo test --verbose`
3. `cargo fmt -- --check`
4. `cargo clippy --verbose -- -D warnings`

