## 7. Build, Dev & Deployment

All commands from `sys-monitor-tauri/`:

```powershell
# Install frontend deps
npm install

# Full dev (Vite + Tauri hot-reload)
npm run tauri dev

# Production bundle (.msi / .exe)
npm run tauri build

# Frontend only in browser (mock data, no Rust)
npm run dev                       # http://127.0.0.1:5180

# Rust unit tests
cd src-tauri && cargo test

# Rust lint
cd src-tauri && cargo clippy -- -D warnings

# Rust format check
cd src-tauri && cargo fmt -- --check

# TypeScript type check
npx tsc --noEmit
```

**Critical config values**:
- Vite dev server: port **5180** (strict port; in `vite.config.ts` and `tauri.conf.json`)
- Tauri window: 900√ó1100 default, 400√ó300 minimum
- Bundle identifier: `com.sysmonitor.app`
- Release profile: `opt-level = 3`, `lto = true`, `codegen-units = 1`, `strip = true`

**No environment variables required** ‚Äî all configuration is compile-time.

---

## 8. Key Domain Knowledge

- `nvidia_temp` on `MetricsSnapshot` is a legacy top-level field; GPU-specific temp is now on `GpuSnapshot.temp_c`
- First PDH reading after init is always `0%` ‚Äî by design (baseline establishment)
- Card order in `App.tsx` resets on launch ‚Äî no persistence by design
- Disk keys are drive-letter combos (`"C:"`, `"C: D:"`) parsed from PDH instance names like `"0 C: D:"`
- GPU display names are brand-stripped (`"NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4050"` ‚Üí `"GeForce RTX 4050"`) via `strip_brand_prefix`
- GPU LUIDs are machine-specific, change across reboots ‚Äî never hardcode them
- `WMI retry`: exponential backoff, base 1s, max 30s, 8 attempts
- `SafeAppState = SafeHistoryStore = Mutex<HistoryStore>` ‚Äî all the same type alias
